#Text=Luis A. Aguilar
#Text=Luis
#Text=A.
#Text=Aguilar
#Text=is an American lawyer and former U.S. government official .
#Text=He was the Democratic commissioner of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission ( SEC ) from July 31 , 2008 , until June 2015 ( when his term expired ) .
#Text=He had been appointed by U.S. President George W. Bush on March 31 , 2008 , and confirmed by the U.S. Senate on June 27 , 2008 ; he was sworn in as a commissioner on July 31 , 2008 .
#Text=Early life and education
#Text=Aguilar was born in Cuba and emigrated to the United States in the 1960s .
#Text=He is a graduate of the University of Georgia School of Law , and also received a Master of Laws degree in taxation from Emory University .
#Text=He had earlier earned a bachelor 's degree from Georgia Southern University .
#Text=Career
#Text=Prior to his appointment as an SEC commissioner , Aguilar was a partner with the international law firm of McKenna Long & Aldridge , specializing in securities law .

#Text=During his career , his practice included matters pertaining to general corporate and business law , international transactions , investment companies and investment advisers , securities law , and corporate finance .

#Text=He also focused on issues related to corporate governance , public and private offerings ( initial public offerings and secondary market offerings ) , mergers and acquisitions , mutual funds , investment advisers , broker-dealers , and other aspects of federal and state securities laws and regulations .

#Text=Aguilar 's previous experience includes serving as the general counsel , executive vice president , and corporate secretary of the investment management company Invesco , with responsibility for all legal and compliance matters regarding Invesco Institutional .
#Text=He also was Invesco 's managing director for Latin America in the late 1990s .
#Text=His career also includes tenure as a partner at several national law firms and as an attorney at SEC .
#Text=Aguilar 's term at the SEC expired in June 2015 . [ 1 ]
#Text=Other activities
#Text=He has been active in numerous civic and business associations .
#Text=From May 2005 to May 2007 , he chaired the Latin American Association ( LAA ) , a non-profit organization .
#Text=He has been active with national organizations , including Hispanic National Bar Association .

#Text=In 2002 , Aguilar was co-chair of the association 's annual convention and also served as regional president ( for Georgia , Alabama , and Mississippi ) ( 2002 – 2006 ) , chair of its financial committee ( 2003 – 2005 ) , and a member of its board of governors ( since 2002 ) .
#Text=In addition , he served as the president of the Hispanic National Bar Foundation ( September 2006 – July 2008 ) .
#Text=Aguilar serves as sponsor of the SEC 's Hispanic Employment Committee and the African American Council .
#Text=Honors
#Text=Aguilar was named by Hispanic Business magazine in 2006 as one of the " 100 Influential " Hispanics in the United States .
#Text=Additionally , he was named Member of the Year in 2005 and the Atlanta Hispanic Businessman of the Year in 1994 by the Georgia Hispanic Chamber of Commerce .
#Text=He received the MALDEF 's " Excellence in Leadership " Award in April 2005 .

column1: #Text=He was also named the 2005 Latino Attorney of the Year by the Hispanic National Bar Association .
#Text=In January 2007 , Aguilar received the Justice Robert Benham Award for Community Service by the Chief Justice 's Commission on Professionalism of the Supreme Court of Georgia .
#Text=Personal life
#Text=He is married to Denise Traylor Aguilar who hails from Roanoke , Alabama .
